      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAPER SHREDDER (1) jumped from a squeeze box last start but was quickly into stride and led throughout to score (22.73) at this track in a Grade 4/5 over 400m. Goes very well from this draw with five wins and four minor placings from 11 starts. Looks the one to beat. STOP IT ZIPPER (2) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 2 lengths at this track in a handy 22.96 beating Make Your Stand. The form out of his last race has been franked. One of the key runners again. MAEVE BABY (4) comes off a solid 22.84 placing at this track over 400m. Harder here but expected to measure up. DAPHNE ZACAPA (7) should be thereabouts after filling a top-three spot in a fast run most recently.",
